Serves: 8 - 10Difficulty: Easy, 3 hours plus overnight for settingIngredients:250ml (1 cup) fresh cream5ml (1 tsp) vanilla extract a 385g can condensed milkFinely grated zest and juice of 1 small lemon100g blanched almonds, toasted and chopped500ml (2 cups) ready-made custard1 x 800g can canned fruit salad, drained1 medium can crushed pineapple, drained80ml (1/3 cup) raspberry or strawberry jam1 packet shortbread biscuits80ml (1/3 cup) sherry or brandy1 x 80g red jelly1 x 80g green jelly1 x 80g yellow jellyRich Christmas fruit cakeIngredients:1) Line a large loaf pan with clingfilm, leaving enough overhang to cover the top of the trifle.2) Beat the cream and vanilla together till thick. Stir in the condensed milk, lemon zest and juice. Pour into the prepared loaf pan, sprinkle over the toasted almonds and freeze until just beginning to set.3) Remove from freezer, pour over the custard and top with canned fruit salad and crushed pineapple. Freeze again until just setting.4) Remove from freezer and spoon dollops of jam over the custard layer. Dip each shortbread biscuit in the sherry or brandy and arrange on top of the jam. Cover with clingfilm and freeze.5) Make each jelly separately, stirring each packet into 225ml boiling water till dissolved. Pour into separate square containers, cover with clingwrap and refrigerate overnight.6) Remove the trifle from the freezer 30 minutes before serving. When softened enough, turn out onto a serving platter so the biscuits are at the bottom. Cut the jellies into cubes and sprinkle over the top of the trifle. Slice and serve with extra cream or custard if desired.